description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the new North East prison contract, there is an exciting opportunity for an experienced clinician to lead a team of multi-disciplinary professionals within HMP Low Newton; a youth offenders and adult female prison situated in Durham. We are looking for someone who is experienced, innovative and an inspirational leader to provide both clinical and operational management to the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Team Manager, you will have the opportunity to work with different stakeholders which includes working with other Healthcare Providers, service users, families and other agencies, therefore strong team working principles are essential. As a leader in the service, you will be responsible for championing the improvement of our patients experience and ensuring that we are providing patient centred care, as well as helping shape our teams for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within Health &amp; Justice, you will receive support from the Locality Manager and can access the peer support group with the other Team Managers. As a service we are dedicated to staff wellbeing and have weekly training slots for CPD as well as other development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require the post holders to be committed to equal opportunities and non-discriminatory practices and reflect the trust values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact details; Phil Flanagan - Philip.flanagan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hayley Todd, Assistant Locality Manager hayleytodd1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
